Six solders, including a colonel and a captain were said to have been killed by Boko Haram insurgents in an ambush along Maiduguri- Damaturu road on Wednesday. A security source, who did not want his name in print, told our correspondent that; “on Wednesday July 17, 2019 at about 17:21 hours, a military gun truck was ambushed by Boko Haram terrorists between Benesheik and Jakana, killing all six occupants, including a Colonel, a captain and their escorts.” He said: “ A search and rescue team was deployed to the scene of the incident, where the bodies of a Colonel, a captain ( names withheld) and four others were recovered. “One of the soldiers who escaped the ambush ran back to Benesheik. A reinforcements  of troops was deployed to the area to trail the insurgents “, the source added. All efforts to get the Spokesman of the Operation Lafiya Dole, Col. Ado Isa, for confirmation proved abortive, as his telephone line was not reachable.